  "description": "Issue #11 slice 1 (+review-fix round): title-screen SELECT+R hotkey opens the debug hub, whose only entry is the built-in 'Fast Boot: Prologue' launcher. The intro sequence (Health & Safety screen + logos) masks all input via gKeyStatusIgnoredSt until it clears, and Title_IDLE itself only becomes reachable/interactive after the standard A/START intro-advance taps (mirrors title-progression.json's own input sequence through its 'intro-menu-progression' checkpoint) -- so the hotkey is deliberately pulsed well after those taps complete (frame 600), not immediately at boot. This scenario deliberately pulses SELECT+R TWICE (600-606, then 650-656, replicating a reviewer-reproduced release-and-repress) with the hub already open before the second pulse: hubOpenCount must stay exactly 1 across both pulses (DebugTools_OpenHub's reentrancy guard rejects the second call with DEBUGTOOLS_ERR_ALREADY_ACTIVE, a no-op) -- proving a repeated hotkey pulse can never spawn a second concurrent hub MenuProc. Only after both pulses does an A press (700-706) select the hub's one entry. Probes read gDebugToolsProbe (include/expansion_debugtools.h) directly by its modern-debug link address: hubOpenCount, registeredActionCount, lastRegisterResult, launcherArmed (DEBUGTOOLS_LAUNCHER_ARMED_MAGIC / 'DBL1'), titleIdleTimerSample -- stable state/probe evidence, not input playback alone.",
